The Israeli Army and Police officials have told media correspondents that 4 rockets were fired on Israeli territory from Lebanon, of which one fell into the town of Neharia in northern Israel, slightly injuring two people.
Israeli artillery has bombarded Lebanon in answer to the rockets fired from Lebanese territory.
It is not clear whether this attack was carried out by Hizbullah or the Palestinian groups active in Lebanon.
The Lebanese government says that it is also trying to determine who is behind these rocket attacks.
BBC correspondents have declared that this as a very dangerous development in the region's current situation.
The BBC's editor for the Middle East, Jeremy Bowen, stated that because of these rocket attacks the danger of the war spreading has increased.
Over the past few days, fears have risen that the military operation in Gaza may extend further north, along the Lebanon- Israel border
There, on Wednesday night, the Israeli Air Force conducted sixty air raids on Gaza Strip.
According to the Israeli Army, these attacks targeted the offices of Hamas's Police Force's, underground tunnels, weapons' caches, rocket launching sites and armed Hamas personnel.
Apart from air raids, Israel's Army and Navy artillery continued shelling Gaza during the night.
The Palestinian Authorities said that a mosque was destroyed during the air raids on the Gaza city.
According to unconfirmed reports, Israeli tanks, with helicopter air support, have advanced towards the area of Khan Younus.
