3.5 Million Users Affected by Virus
Discovered for the first time in October 2008, this virus known by the names like Confecker, Down and Up and Kido.
Microsoft has released a patch to tackle with this virus. Despite that, almost 3.5 million computer and memory sticks have been affected with it.
The experts say that the number of affected computers can be a lot more.
To handle this, the users need to use Microsoft's MS08067 patch.
According to Microsoft, this virus which infected millions of computers, locates the services.exe file in Windows and then gets into its code.
Afterwards, this virus turns into a DLL type of file into the System folder of Windows.
It also creates the name of this file as well.
Then it changes the registry details of Windows.
After getting activated, this virus creates a problem which rises as an http server and changes the restore point of the system.
Afterwards, it downloads the files from the maker's website.
According to Microsoft, this virus has infected computers in different countries of the world.
These countries include China, Brazil, Russia, India, America and Britain.
