Tea: A potential cure for breast cancer?
According to new research, drinking three cups of tea every day
reduced the chances of breast cancer by more than one third  in women less than 50 years old.
In research conducted by the Moffitt Cancer Center in Florida in the United States, it has been found that women less than 50 years old that have the breast cancer oncogene
reduced their chances of breast cancer by 37 percent among those who drank three cups of tea a day.
The research indicated that older women did not get any benefit from drinking three or more cups of tea a day.
The researchers think that the tea contains polyphenols that are effective against the type of oncogene in the breast cancer that affects women younger than 50.
The Moft Cancer Center in Tampa, Florida, studied 5,000 women who had taken the treatment for breast cancer.
Their ages were between 20 and 70 years.
The experts compared their medical records and lifestyle with those of women who have not been diagnosed with breast cancer.
The experts also found out that on a particular type of breast cancer called Lobular, tea had shown to prevent cancer by 66%.
Almost one in ten patients of breast cancer suffer from this type.
This type of cancer is more dangerous because it deep inside and is usually diagnosed when it has already spread to a great extent.
Experts say that by drinking at least three cups of tea a day, the danger of breast cancer can be reduced in young women.
They say that making tea a regular drink can cause great resistance in the body against breast cancer.
In Britain every year almost 40,000 women are diagnosed with breast cancer.
The Afghan war is the greatest challenge faced by America : Gates.
American Defense Minister Robert Gates has said that the war in Afghanistan is the biggest military challenge faced by America.
Gates will give a briefing today to the Senate and House over the strategies of the Obama office on the Afghanistan and Iraq wars.
