Most of the elders from our family belonged to the labor community.
In our childhood, when we used to see our uncles doing labor work, we used to pray to Allah to save us from this hard work.
To avoid this, we wrote a letter to the editor of the daily Amroz and asked him what we should we do after matriculation so that we don't have to do labor work.
The editor wrote in reply that we should select certain subjects and become doctors or engineers.
Right from beginning, my trend was towards engineering. I had selected technical drawing instead of Biology as well.
But at the time of admission in F.Sc. my elder brother forced me to become a doctor after doing F.Sc. in medical.
I studied biology for a month and then took math as an alternate subject when nothing worked out.
The fear of labor work made me an engineer and now I am in a better position than other in my family, for which I am always thankful to God.
